#Text=Wikinews interviews Frank McEnulty , independent candidate for US President
#Text=Saturday , February 16 , 2008

#Text=While nearly all cover of the 2008 Presidential election has focused on the Democratic and Republican candidates , there are small political parties offering candidates , and those who choose to run without a party behind them , independents .
#Text=Wikinews is interviewing some of these citizens who are looking to become the 43rd person elected to serve their nation from 1600 Pennsylvania Avenue NW .
#Text=First off is Long Beach , California 's Frank McEnulty ( b. 1956 ) , a married father of two with an MBA ( Venture Management ) and BS ( Accounting/Finance ) .
#Text=Interview
#Text=Why do you want to be President ?
#Text=My name is Frank McEnulty and I am running as an independent candidate for President of the United States in 2008 .
#Text=Crazy right ?
#Text=Well maybe , but I am just way too fed up with how the two major parties are running ( or should I say ruining ) politics in this country and I feel the need to try and do something about it .
#Text=I 've noticed over the past several years that most of the political ads are pushing a party , rather than ideas or an individual .
#Text=" Vote for me , I 'm a Republican " or " Vote for me , I 'm a Democrat " is all one seems to hear any more .
#Text=What do these people stand for ?
#Text=Nothing until the party tells them to or else they get cut off from the fountain of money .
#Text=Do these candidates have independent thoughts ?
#Text=Maybe , but they never voice them in public because it might not be in line with party doctrine .
#Text=Do they ever vote for a bill , law or policy because it is the right thing to do for the country ?
#Text=Only if the party tells them it is okay to do so .
#Text=Usually , if a Republican introduces a piece of legislation it must be wrong per the Democrats because the Democrats did n’t come up with it .
#Text=Usually , if a Democrat introduces a piece of legislation it must be wrong per the Republicans because the Republicans did n’t come up with it .
#Text=What ’s wrong with just working together to do what is right for the country regardless of what party you are affiliated with ?
#Text=If you ’re as disillusioned with how the political process seems to be working as I am let ’s get together and make them see how upset we are .
#Text=None of us can do it by ourselves , but if enough of us band together we can and will make them sit up and take notice .

#Text=Please visit my website at www.frankforpresident.org to see where I stand on a lot of today ’s important issues and pass this email along to all your family members and friends , co-workers and everyone else you know .
